cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a data augmentation method for natural language processing tasks, specifically sentence classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the effectiveness of the proposed method on improving the predictive accuracy of state-of-the-art networks, which suggests a focus on machine learning and deep learning techniques. This makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper uses benchmark datasets and evaluates the proposed method's performance, which suggests a focus on evaluation and experimentation, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) possible sub-categories as well.
